# Q39. Theory – IoT Gateway

An **IoT Gateway** is a device that acts as a bridge between IoT sensor nodes and the cloud. It collects data from multiple sensors, performs basic processing or filtering, converts data between different communication protocols if needed, and securely sends the data to cloud servers. The gateway also receives commands from the cloud and forwards them to the appropriate IoT devices. Using a gateway improves security, reduces network traffic, and allows devices with different communication technologies to work together.

### Simple IoT Architecture Diagram

```
+----------------+     Wi-Fi / LoRa / Zigbee / BLE      +---------------+
| IoT Sensor     | -----------------------------------> |  IoT Gateway  |
| Nodes          |                                      |               |
+----------------+                                      +---------------+
                                                               |
                                                               | MQTT / HTTP / HTTPS
                                                               |
                                                               v
                                                        +---------------+
                                                        |     Cloud     |
                                                        | IoT Platform  |
                                                        +---------------+
                                                               |
                                                               | HTTPS / REST API
                                                               |
                                                               v
                                                       +------------------+
                                                       | User Application |
                                                       | Web / Mobile App |
                                                       +------------------+
```

### Protocols Used at Each Layer

| Layer                          | Common Protocols                                |
| ------------------------------ | ----------------------------------------------- |
| **IoT Sensor Nodes → Gateway** | LoRa, Zigbee, Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE), Wi-Fi |
| **Gateway → Cloud**            | MQTT, HTTP, HTTPS, CoAP                         |
| **Cloud → User Application**   | HTTPS, REST API, WebSocket                      |


